commit 4a725074967ca1a9413b86ca911319e4928324ac
Author: gretjia <gretjia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 22 11:46:21 2026 +0000

    experiment/phase-8 R1-α + R2 + R3: Ed25519 receipt, durable WAL, nested comments
    
    Addresses Codex re-audit VETO (R1 still broken) + residual CHALLENGEs (R2, R3).
    
    R1-α (was R1 VETO — capability forgeable):
      Replaced the nonce-based "capability" with real Ed25519 signatures.
      - OracleReceipt now carries (issuer_pub, signature) over the canonical
        message (payload_hash || context_hash || kind || verdict_encoding).
        Fields are private; only `sign_new` constructs. Receipt is
        cryptographically bound to the signing key — forging requires breaking
        Ed25519, not just owning `&mut Bus`.
      - Lean4Oracle now holds a per-instance SigningKey (private); exposes
        `public_key()`, `issue_complete_receipt()`, `issue_partial_receipt()`.
      - TuringBus replaces `registered_oracle_nonces: HashSet<u64>` with
        `trusted_oracle_pubs: HashSet<[u8; 32]>` + `oracles_frozen: bool`.
      - `register_oracle` now returns Result; Err if called after init()
        (oracles_frozen freeze gate). Closes Codex's "attacker with &mut Bus
        registers own pubkey, then signs, then submits" attack path.
      - `init()` and `with_wal_path` (after non-empty replay) both freeze.
      - evaluator.rs refactored: single persistent `oracle` per run_swarm /
        run_oneshot, registered BEFORE init, cloned for tool-mount. Removed
        per-tx oracle creation.
      - New tests (`tests/oracle_receipt_bus.rs`, 8 total):
          * accepts_matching_receipt
          * rejects_hash_mismatch
          * rejects_reject_verdict
          * partial_ok_succeeds
          * rejects_unregistered_issuer        ← R1-α key test
          * rejects_cross_context_replay
          * post_init_register_oracle_fails    ← R1-α freeze test
          * attacker_with_mut_bus_cannot_forge_post_init ← Codex attack replay
      - Crate dep: `ed25519-dalek = "2"` in both turingosv4 + minif2f_v4.
    
    R2 (was CHALLENGE — oneshot WAL fallback silent):
      Removed the in-memory fallback when `TuringBus::with_wal_path` fails.
      Instead, emit `MEASUREMENT_ERROR oneshot WAL: <e>` and return a
      non-result PputResult (condition=measurement_error, solved=false, tx=1).
      Batch runner should retry. Preserves C-067 durability invariant:
      ANY oneshot that claims OMEGA has a durable WAL Halt event.
    
    R3 (was CHALLENGE — nested block comments):
      `strip_strings_and_comments` now tracks nesting depth for `/- ... -/`
      blocks. Correct Lean grammar: openings increment, closings decrement,
      only depth==0 terminates stripping. Doc comments (`/--`, `/-!`) enter
      the same branch and strip correctly.
      New tests: `handles_nested_block_comments`, `handles_doc_comments`.
    
    Test counts (post-R1α/R2/R3):
      turingosv4 lib:            120/120 ✅ (+1 Ed25519 receipt tampered-sig test)
      minif2f_v4 lib:             26/26  ✅ (+2 nested + doc comments)
      oracle_receipt_bus:          8/8   ✅ NEW (Ed25519 contract)
      snapshot_nonempty:           7/7   ✅
      q_halt_state:                8/8   ✅
      reputation:                  9/9   ✅
      rejection_threshold:         5/5   ✅
      wal_resume:                  2/2   ✅
      reward_pull_conservation:    3/5   pre-existing (Phase 8.Z)
    
    Refs:
      handover/audits/EXT_CODEX_PHASE_8_R1R8_2026-04-22.md (VETO drove R1-α)
      handover/audits/EXT_GEMINI_PHASE_8_R1R8_2026-04-22.md (R1-R8 PASS)
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

